  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"workouts\":[{\"day_of_week\":1,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":8,\"target_duration_minutes\":52,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":392,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":392,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":403,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start at the relaxed end of easy pace. Let the body settle in for the first 5 minutes before finding your rhythm.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":42,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":392,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Hold a conversational pace throughout. You should be able to speak in full sentences. Stay in the 5:52 to 6:43 per km range from your Daniels-Gilbert zones.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":403,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Ease off in the final 5 minutes. Walk the last 60 to 90 seconds if needed.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"No specific warmup drills required. A few minutes of walking before you start counts.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk 1 to 2 minutes after finishing. Do a short hip flexor and calf stretch, given your IT band history.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"This run builds your aerobic base without adding stress. The purpose is blood flow and adaptation, not fitness stimulus. Keep the effort genuinely easy. Your current pace-zone index of 42.0 places your easy range at 5:52 to 6:43 per km. Err toward the slower end on Monday. The week starts here.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"title\":\"Threshold Cruise Intervals\",\"target_distance_km\":9,\"target_duration_minutes\":55,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":392,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":293,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":12,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":403,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog for 12 minutes. Include 4 to 6 short strides in the final 2 minutes to prime the legs before threshold work.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":8,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":293,\"intensity\":\"Threshold\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"First threshold cruise interval. Target 4:53 per km from your Daniels-Gilbert zones. This should feel comfortably hard. You can speak a word or two but not a sentence.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Recovery\",\"duration_minutes\":2,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":403,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog recovery. Let the breathing settle but keep moving.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":8,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":293,\"intensity\":\"Threshold\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Second threshold cruise interval. Same effort and pace as the first. Stay relaxed in the shoulders and face.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Recovery\",\"duration_minutes\":2,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":403,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog recovery between intervals.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":8,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":293,\"intensity\":\"Threshold\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Third threshold cruise interval. If the pace feels forced, back off slightly. Consistency across all three intervals matters more than hitting the number exactly.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":15,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":403,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog cooldown. Gradually reduce effort. Finish with a short walk.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"12 minutes easy jog. Add 4 to 6 strides of 20 seconds at roughly half-marathon effort in the last 2 minutes of the warmup.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"15 minutes easy jog back to base effort. Walk 2 minutes at the end. Stretch IT band and hip flexors afterward.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Cruise intervals at threshold pace develop your lactate clearance capacity, which is the key physiological driver for a strong half-marathon. Three times 8 minutes at 4:53 per km with 2-minute jog recoveries is a moderate but productive stimulus for your current fitness. This is the most important workout of the week. Do not skip it in favor of doing more easy miles.\",\"perceived_effort\":7},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Recovery Easy Run\",\"target_distance_km\":6,\"target_duration_minutes\":40,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":403,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":403,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":40,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":403,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Run at the slow end of your Daniels-Gilbert easy zone, 6:30 to 6:43 per km. This is active recovery from Wednesday threshold work. The goal is loose legs, not training stimulus.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"No formal warmup needed. Start easy and stay easy.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk 2 minutes at the end. Light stretching on the IT band and glutes.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"The day after threshold work, easy running accelerates recovery by increasing blood flow without adding meaningful load. Keep the pace honest. If your legs feel heavy, slower is correct, not a failure.\",\"perceived_effort\":3},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"workout_type\":\"Interval\",\"title\":\"VO2Max Intervals\",\"target_distance_km\":10,\"target_duration_minutes\":58,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":392,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":270,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":15,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":392,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog for 15 minutes. Include 4 strides of 20 seconds at interval pace in the final 3 minutes to prepare the neuromuscular system.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":3,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":270,\"intensity\":\"VO2Max\",\"repetitions\":5,\"notes\":\"Five repetitions of 3 minutes at 4:30 per km from your Daniels-Gilbert zones. This is hard but controlled. Not a sprint. You should feel like you could hold this pace for about 10 minutes total. Take 2-minute easy jog between each rep.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Recovery\",\"duration_minutes\":2,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":403,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":4,\"notes\":\"2-minute easy jog between each work interval. Keep moving. Do not stop.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":15,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":403,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"15 minutes easy jog. Gradual deceleration. Walk the final 90 seconds.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"15 minutes easy jog followed by 4 short strides. The warmup is non-negotiable before interval work.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"15 minutes easy jog. Walk 2 minutes. Stretch hip flexors, calves, and IT band.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"VO2max intervals at 4:30 per km build your aerobic ceiling, which creates headroom for your half-marathon goal of 1:45. Five times 3 minutes is a moderate dose for your current fitness. The total interval time of 15 minutes is appropriate given your training age and recent volume. This workout is demanding. If you need to drop a rep to maintain quality, do that rather than grinding through a degraded effort.\",\"perceived_effort\":8},{\"day_of_week\":0,\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"title\":\"Long Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":16,\"target_duration_minutes\":100,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":403,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":392,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":10,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":403,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start at the slow end of easy pace for the first 10 minutes. Do not rush the warmup phase of a long run.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":80,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":392,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Steady easy pace in the 5:52 to 6:43 per km Daniels-Gilbert zone. Aim for the middle of the range. The final 20 to 25 minutes may feel harder. That is normal. Maintain form rather than pace if needed.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":10,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":403,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Ease down in the final 10 minutes. Finish with a walk.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Begin with 5 minutes of walking or very slow jogging. The long run warm-up is built into the first mile of the run itself.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk 3 to 5 minutes after finishing. Prioritize hydration. Stretch IT band, hip flexors, and calves. Given your IT band history, a foam roll on the lateral quad is worth doing today.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"The long run is the structural core of half-marathon training. At 16 km this week, you are taking a measured step up from your recent 14 km. The aerobic adaptation from extended time on feet is the primary stimulus. Pace is secondary. Do not let this become a moderate-effort run. It should feel easy for the first two thirds. Carrying water or a gel is a good habit to build at this duration.\",\"perceived_effort\":5}]}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "modelId": "\"claude-sonnet-4-6\"",
